[4] Cholera, diarrhea - Nepal (Central Region)
Date: Wed 11 Jul 2007
Source: Rising Nepal [edited]
<http://www.gorkhapatra.org.np/content.php?nid=22836>

The [number of] patients with cholera and gastroenteritis has gone up
at and around the areas of Lalitpur sub-metropolis, said District
Public Health Office, Lalitpur. Around 62 out of 508 patients of
diarrhea visiting hospital between 15 Jun and 10 Jul 2007 have been
detected with cholera, said Senior Public Health Officer Rishi Prasad
Lamichhane.
The Public Health Office has launched a special program following the
rise [in the number] of patients of cholera and diarrhea at and
around the sub-metropolis area. The office has taken initiatives to
examine the quality of drinking water, to create awareness among
people, and to dispatch medicines to the respective health posts at
the area, informed Lamichhane.
Likewise, the office is set to launch a massive public awareness
program on how to prevent epidemics of cholera in the area, in
coordination with the sub-metropolis, local social organisations, and
the District Education Office. The office has started the task of
examining and purifying water at stone spouts and wells, the main
sources of drinking water at the area.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Lalitpur, also called Patan, is located south of Katmandu in the
Central Region of Nepal and can be found at
<http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm>. - Mod.LL]
