[5] Cholera - Nepal (Central Region)
Date: Fri 20 Jul 2007
Source: Kantipur Online [edited]
<http://www.kantipuronline.com/kolnews.php?&nid=116505>

A teenager has died and 7 others have fallen seriously ill due to an
outbreak of cholera in a [remote] village in the northern part of
Dolakha district over the week.
The 13-year-old girl, a resident of Sungure in Lapelang VDC-9, passed
away Friday morning [20 Jul 2007], while undergoing treatment at the
village.
According to a health worker Jagat Bahadur Khadka, 3 patients in
serious condition have been referred to the district headquarters
after they were treated in the village. Khadka also said the patients
apparently were suffering from cholera, as they showed no sign of
improvement even after administering medicines and saline water
throughout the night.
According to [the Kantipur] correspondent, an entire locality in the
village has been affected following the outbreak of gastroenteritis.
The District Health Office has informed that a team of health workers
and some medicines have been dispatched to the affected village.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Dolakha is located in the extreme northeast corner of the Central
Region of Nepal bordering Tibet to its north and can be found
(spelled Dolkha) at
<http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm>. - Mod.LL]
