[6] Diarrhea - Indonesia (Banten)
Date: Tue 17 Jul 2007
Source: The Jakarta Post [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailcity.asp?fileid=20070717.C03&irec=2>
(archived)

A total of 4 children have now died in an outbreak of diarrhea in
Tangerang regency, which has affected 5 districts. The head of the
communicable diseases prevention unit at the regency's health agency,
Yuliah Iskandar, said Mon 16 Jul 2007, that 2 children in Lebak Wangi
village and another in Sarakan village, both in Sepatan district, had
died of dehydration over the weekend [14-15 Jul 2007]. The 1st death
was of a 2-year-old girl on Thu 12 Jul 2007, after being treated at a
health clinic for several hours.
According to the agency, 487 people, mostly children, have been
treated for diarrhea at public health clinics in Sepatan, Kedaung
Barat, and Pakuhaji districts. The overwhelmed clinics have been
forced to set up tents to accommodate all of the patients.
While Regent Ismet Iskandar earlier blamed residents and their lack
of understanding of proper sanitation for the outbreak, Yuliah said
the outbreak was not caused by contaminated water used in their
homes. "We have examined water taken from the residents' wells and it
is free from the _E. coli_ and _Vibrio cholerae_ bacteria that have
caused the outbreak," she said.
Patients interviewed by health agency officials, she said, consumed
snacks and iced syrup beverages purchased from street vendors before
falling ill. "We have sent a sample of the syrup for laboratory tests
and we will announce the results as soon as possible," Yuliah said.
The outbreak began early last week [8-14 Jul 2007] in Sepatan
district, spreading to Sepatan Timur, Pakuhaji, Rajeg, and Sukadiri
districts. The Tangerang regency administration has declared the
diarrhea outbreak an "extraordinary occurrence" in the 5 districts.
In June 2005, a similar outbreak affected more than 1000 people,
killing 19.
[Byline: Multa Fidrus]
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett
[The speculation regarding the syrup beverages as a cause of this
outbreak is likely to be unfounded and the inability to isolate
pathogens from the water supply does not eliminate contaminated water
as a vehicle.
Tangerang Regency is a regency of Banten province, Indonesia. It is
part of Jabotabek, the metropolitan area surrounding Jakarta. The
proximity to Jakarta can be found on a map at
<http://www.weather-forecast.com/locationmaps/Tangerang.jpg>.
A map of the provinces of Indonesia can be found at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image:Indonesia_provinces_english.png> - Mod.LL]
