[8] Cholera - China (Guandong)
Date: Wed 20 Jun 2007 [This moderator apologizes for the delay in
posting. - Mod.LL]
Source: News365 [in Chinese, trans. Rappt.DS, edited]
<http://www.news365.com.cn/xwzx/gn/200706/t20070620_1460214.htm>

On the afternoon of 19 Jun 2007, Guandong Provincial Health Bureau
announced that Guangzhou Municipal Health Bureau reported 2 confirmed
cases of cholera in Guangzhou's Liwan District on 16 and 17 Jun 2007.
An investigation showed that both patients serve as nannies in a
Liwan District household. On 13 Jun 2007, they developed low-grade
fever, diarrhea, and other symptoms. Lab analysis was positive for
_Vibrio cholerae_ (Inaba type). Prior to becoming ill, the patients
had eaten blue crab, freshwater prawns, and other food. There is a
high likelihood that food was the source of infection.
[Byline: Xia Yang]
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Dan Silver
[Guandong Province is in southeastern China and can be found
highlighted on the map at
<http://www.hokkian-siauwlim.de/guandong.jpg>. - Mod.LL]
