[11] Shigellosis - USA (Kentucky, Ohio)
Date: Wed 4 Jul 2007
Source: WCPO, Cincinnati (OH) [edited]
<http://www.wcpo.com/news/local/story.aspx?content_id=4443fa5f-9fdf-458a-8ca4-84443f85bd4f>

Health officials say the Tri-state is experiencing an outbreak of
shigellosis [a disease caused by the bacterium _Shigella_.
It can be treated with antibiotics and generally subsides in about 5
days. Symptoms include diarrhea, abdominal pain, cramping, and fever
-- especially in young children.
There have been more than 80 cases reported in Northern Kentucky, and
the Cincinnati (Ohio) Health Department investigated more than 120
cases in May and June 2007.
[Byline: Neil Relyea]
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The 3rd state referred to is Indiana, although no cases are
mentioned from there. The states (OH, KY & IN) can be seen on a
USA map at
<http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/USclimate/states.fast.html>. - Mod.LL]
